# Keep the Docker build context lean and deterministic. Anything here is NOT sent to
# the daemon, so it can't leak into or poison an image layer.

# Dependencies + build output are reinstalled/recompiled inside the image.
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/.turbo

# 🚨 CRITICAL: exclude TS incremental build state. The buildable shared package
# (@app/contracts) pins composite:false/incremental:false so it ALWAYS emits, but a
# STALE *.tsbuildinfo copied from the host would make tsc believe it already emitted
# and SKIP emission inside the image — leaving an empty dist that breaks every consumer
# in a hard-to-diagnose way. Stripping it here guarantees a clean emit in Docker.
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Test + coverage artifacts: never needed at runtime.
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
**/*.test.ts
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.int.test.ts
**/*.prop.test.ts
**/*.eval.test.ts
e2e

# VCS, CI, and docs are irrelevant to the runtime image.
.git
.github
docs
terraform
*.md

# Never bake real secrets/env into an image; keep only the template.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
